WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.288 --> 00:00:02.869
<v ->Wilhelm Reich was one of the most original thinkers</v>

2
00:00:02.869 --> 00:00:05.706
of the last century, yet few know his name.

3
00:00:05.706 --> 00:00:07.168
As with many other pioneers

4
00:00:07.168 --> 00:00:09.141
in the fields of science and medicine,

5
00:00:09.141 --> 00:00:11.093
Reich was too far ahead of his peers

6
00:00:11.093 --> 00:00:13.791
to be allowed to flourish, but today,

7
00:00:13.791 --> 00:00:15.156
50 years after his death,

8
00:00:15.156 --> 00:00:17.193
James Demeo is picking up the gauntlet

9
00:00:17.193 --> 00:00:20.436
and uses Reich's principles to take humanity forward,

10
00:00:20.436 --> 00:00:23.689
including our understanding of sex and economics.

11
00:00:23.689 --> 00:00:28.291
(ethereal music)

12
00:00:32.915 --> 00:00:36.809
<v Regina>Wilhelm Reich is a very much misunderstood</v>

13
00:00:36.809 --> 00:00:41.235
person in the history of understanding life force energy.

14
00:00:41.235 --> 00:00:44.599
And you have really made it your life's work to understand

15
00:00:44.599 --> 00:00:47.437
what this man was doing to be able to connect dots

16
00:00:47.437 --> 00:00:52.150
and bring it into common modern culture today.

17
00:00:52.150 --> 00:00:54.977
Let's talk about first his beginning

18
00:00:54.977 --> 00:00:56.620
in association with Freud

19
00:00:56.620 --> 00:00:57.879
before we go into yours.

20
00:00:57.879 --> 00:01:01.594
<v ->Okay,</v>

21
00:01:01.594 --> 00:01:03.959
Reich was a refugee

22
00:01:03.959 --> 00:01:06.559
from conditions in World War I.

23
00:01:06.559 --> 00:01:09.942
At the end of the war he came to Vienna,

24
00:01:09.942 --> 00:01:13.530
took a university degree in Medicine,

25
00:01:13.530 --> 00:01:16.368
and his residency was

26
00:01:16.368 --> 00:01:18.708
partly with Sigmund Freud,

27
00:01:18.708 --> 00:01:20.459
he became attracted to Freud's work,

28
00:01:20.459 --> 00:01:22.884
became a devoted psychoanalyst,

29
00:01:22.884 --> 00:01:27.492
and very quickly was brought up in the ranks

30
00:01:27.492 --> 00:01:30.425
of the analytical movement to become one of Freud's

31
00:01:30.425 --> 00:01:34.041
trainers for younger students.

32
00:01:34.041 --> 00:01:37.859
And Reich is well-acknowledged as the leader

33
00:01:37.859 --> 00:01:40.536
of kind of a rebel group within psychoanalysis,

34
00:01:40.536 --> 00:01:44.600
was really looking to make social changes in the world

35
00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:47.587
as a way to prevent neurosis in the first place,

36
00:01:47.587 --> 00:01:51.308
rather than coming after the fact with only therapy.

37
00:01:51.308 --> 00:01:55.405
So that was his start, was in Freudian psychoanalysis,

38
00:01:55.405 --> 00:01:59.938
which is where he got familiar with the idea of libido,

39
00:01:59.938 --> 00:02:04.247
the whole idea of sexual energy or emotional energy,

40
00:02:04.247 --> 00:02:07.745
which, by the way, modern psychoanalysis kind of pu-pu's,

41
00:02:07.745 --> 00:02:11.478
it's not a real essential thing for most of them,

42
00:02:11.478 --> 00:02:14.827
but Reich took this idea of libido very seriously,

43
00:02:14.827 --> 00:02:18.714
and talked about how

44
00:02:18.714 --> 00:02:23.008
people's emotional energy was a real energy,

45
00:02:23.008 --> 00:02:25.415
that their sexual energy

46
00:02:25.415 --> 00:02:28.115
was something that functioned

47
00:02:28.115 --> 00:02:29.470
that required fulfillment

48
00:02:29.470 --> 00:02:32.866
in order for people to have a healthy psyche.

49
00:02:35.806 --> 00:02:38.665
So that was the starting point of his interest in things

50
00:02:38.665 --> 00:02:42.664
like emotional energy or energy dynamics,

51
00:02:42.664 --> 00:02:44.819
biological energy, if you will.

52
00:02:44.819 --> 00:02:46.440
<v Regina>Because that would be certainly one of the most</v>

53
00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:51.055
obvious and pervasive profound energies

54
00:02:51.055 --> 00:02:54.076
that he could begin measuring, even, right?

55
00:02:54.076 --> 00:02:56.935
<v ->Well, absolutely.</v>

56
00:02:56.935 --> 00:02:59.743
And at one point, he broke with Freud.

57
00:02:59.743 --> 00:03:03.950
There was a break, basically on the issue

58
00:03:03.950 --> 00:03:07.706
of the social ramifications of Freud's own theory,

59
00:03:07.706 --> 00:03:11.482
as Reich described it,

60
00:03:11.482 --> 00:03:14.020
that one really needed to have a change in things like

61
00:03:14.020 --> 00:03:16.278
at the time,

62
00:03:16.278 --> 00:03:20.088
women were not getting employed,

63
00:03:20.088 --> 00:03:23.283
the divorce laws, there weren't, divorce was illegal.

64
00:03:23.283 --> 00:03:25.510
Contraception was illegal, so you had

65
00:03:25.510 --> 00:03:28.069
big problems with family and society,

66
00:03:28.069 --> 00:03:30.917
and arranged marriages, loveless conditions,

67
00:03:30.917 --> 00:03:32.912
and a lot of neurosis coming out of this.

68
00:03:32.912 --> 00:03:35.546
Reich wanted to change these things socially.

69
00:03:35.546 --> 00:03:38.639
The Freudians didn't, and of course, then,

70
00:03:38.639 --> 00:03:43.295
the rise of the Nazis, some of the psychoanalysts

71
00:03:43.295 --> 00:03:45.082
felt that they could get along with the Nazis,

72
00:03:45.082 --> 00:03:47.012
Reich said, no, this is a social disaster,

73
00:03:47.012 --> 00:03:49.913
and he fought against them, openly speaking against them,

74
00:03:49.913 --> 00:03:53.048
and was, therefore, forced to flee,

75
00:03:53.048 --> 00:03:57.230
first to Scandinavia and later to the United States,

76
00:03:57.230 --> 00:04:01.176
but during this period of flight, of leaving Austria

77
00:04:01.176 --> 00:04:05.239
and Germany to Denmark and later, Norway,

78
00:04:05.239 --> 00:04:08.974
he did a series of experiments on bioelectricity

79
00:04:08.974 --> 00:04:12.899
where he was attempting to measure

80
00:04:12.899 --> 00:04:16.045
the emotional states of people

81
00:04:16.045 --> 00:04:18.786
and also measuring sexual excitation.

82
00:04:18.786 --> 00:04:21.143
He was long before Masters and Johnson,

83
00:04:21.143 --> 00:04:24.497
Wilhelm Reich was doing this kind of research.

84
00:04:26.487 --> 00:04:30.617
It's an incredibly important body of research,

85
00:04:30.617 --> 00:04:32.389
but I'll summarize.

86
00:04:32.389 --> 00:04:36.732
When people expanded pleasurably,

87
00:04:36.732 --> 00:04:40.090
with like, ahh, great pleasure,

88
00:04:40.090 --> 00:04:42.959
with one's beloved,

89
00:04:42.959 --> 00:04:45.679
the dance of life,

90
00:04:45.679 --> 00:04:49.538
this could be measured as a strong

91
00:04:49.538 --> 00:04:53.645
increase in bioelectrical charge at the skin surface.

92
00:04:53.645 --> 00:04:56.910
And, oppositely,

93
00:04:56.910 --> 00:04:59.550
if a person had a great deal of anxiety,

94
00:04:59.550 --> 00:05:03.416
a great deal of fear, contraction,

95
00:05:03.416 --> 00:05:05.269
which you could see, somatically,

96
00:05:05.269 --> 00:05:07.860
in the way they expressed themself,

97
00:05:07.860 --> 00:05:09.769
if they lived a life of trauma

98
00:05:09.769 --> 00:05:11.049
since the time of their childhood,

99
00:05:11.049 --> 00:05:14.972
and had learned to restrain everything

100
00:05:14.972 --> 00:05:17.266
and to become socialized

101
00:05:17.266 --> 00:05:20.188
in a sex-negative society,

102
00:05:20.188 --> 00:05:21.980
authoritarian society,

103
00:05:21.980 --> 00:05:25.448
then their skin surface would lack that

104
00:05:25.448 --> 00:05:26.866
bioelectrical charge.

105
00:05:26.866 --> 00:05:29.245
They would have a low, weak,

106
00:05:29.245 --> 00:05:31.421
bioelectrical charging at the skin surface

107
00:05:31.421 --> 00:05:35.804
and an incapacity in most cases for pleasurable expansion.

108
00:05:35.804 --> 00:05:39.570
And this is where Reich got the concept of

109
00:05:39.570 --> 00:05:42.801
the psychic and somatic armoring,

110
00:05:42.801 --> 00:05:44.869
or you may hear the term "human armoring."

111
00:05:44.869 --> 00:05:46.327
<v Regina>Mmhmm.</v>
<v James>And this is a term</v>

112
00:05:46.327 --> 00:05:47.494
that Reich developed very early.

113
00:05:47.494 --> 00:05:48.230
<v Regina>And could you</v>

114
00:05:48.230 --> 00:05:49.953
ahead and explain that for us?

115
00:05:49.953 --> 00:05:51.793
<v ->Well armoring is a</v>

116
00:05:51.793 --> 00:05:54.840
a combination of psychological

117
00:05:54.840 --> 00:05:56.687
and somatic...

118
00:05:58.267 --> 00:06:00.097
It's a dynamic

119
00:06:00.097 --> 00:06:04.418
where people are restraining their impulses,

120
00:06:04.418 --> 00:06:07.181
they're restraining their reaching out for things

121
00:06:07.181 --> 00:06:10.936
that they would need, like reaching out for love,

122
00:06:10.936 --> 00:06:15.351
reaching out for the kind of life that they want,

123
00:06:15.351 --> 00:06:18.721
for the kind of work that they would like to do,

124
00:06:18.721 --> 00:06:22.594
so they compromise.

125
00:06:22.594 --> 00:06:26.133
This one I will be with, but I don't really love her,

126
00:06:26.133 --> 00:06:28.897
but she gives me some sexual gratification,

127
00:06:28.897 --> 00:06:30.561
but it isn't really what I want,

128
00:06:30.561 --> 00:06:31.809
or the girl saying,

129
00:06:31.809 --> 00:06:35.696
I really want that guy but, well, so-and-so here is

130
00:06:35.696 --> 00:06:37.984
wanting to be with me,
<v Regina>Has a job.</v>

131
00:06:37.984 --> 00:06:39.264
<v James>He has a job,</v>

132
00:06:39.264 --> 00:06:42.976
all of the excuses that people have for compromising,

133
00:06:42.976 --> 00:06:45.290
their potentials.

134
00:06:45.290 --> 00:06:47.818
Reich was the first one to talk about this,

135
00:06:47.818 --> 00:06:50.293
about the unity of psyche and soma,

136
00:06:50.293 --> 00:06:51.657
that people's character,

137
00:06:51.657 --> 00:06:55.070
their mental process came out of this larger emotional

138
00:06:55.070 --> 00:06:59.095
energetic situation

139
00:06:59.095 --> 00:07:02.545
of their life, and today

140
00:07:02.545 --> 00:07:03.984
you see a lot of people talking about this

141
00:07:03.984 --> 00:07:06.164
in so-called mind-body issues,

142
00:07:06.164 --> 00:07:09.395
and Reich is acknowledged in many places

143
00:07:09.395 --> 00:07:11.945
as the father of these

144
00:07:11.945 --> 00:07:14.415
kinds of ways of viewing

145
00:07:14.415 --> 00:07:18.024
the life, if you will.

146
00:07:18.024 --> 00:07:20.296
And in some cases, he's not acknowledged,

147
00:07:20.296 --> 00:07:23.411
but I think, if you look at Reich's original work,

148
00:07:23.411 --> 00:07:27.229
in books like Function of the Orgasm, or Character Analysis,

149
00:07:27.229 --> 00:07:30.300
which is an interesting book, Character Analysis,

150
00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:33.804
is now used as a teaching text in hospitals

151
00:07:33.804 --> 00:07:38.524
even the psychoanalysts will acknowledge it,

152
00:07:38.524 --> 00:07:41.756
except they'll tell you to stop at part three,

153
00:07:41.756 --> 00:07:43.462
don't read any farther, than part three.

154
00:07:43.462 --> 00:07:46.353
<v Regina>Oh, what's beyond the door there?</v>

155
00:07:46.353 --> 00:07:47.980
<v ->Part three is where he talks about</v>

