Harold Burr, for example,

167
00:08:18.106 --> 00:08:21.146
with the whole electrodynamic field theory,

168
00:08:21.146 --> 00:08:22.532
that was well-known in the fifties,

169
00:08:22.532 --> 00:08:24.132
not so much today.

170
00:08:24.132 --> 00:08:26.659
But he was doing similar bioelectrical measurments

171
00:08:26.659 --> 00:08:30.084
and argued that the bioelectrical fields in people's bodies

172
00:08:30.084 --> 00:08:32.505
could be measured out from their bodies

173
00:08:32.505 --> 00:08:36.227
and that it was an expression of a larger life force,

174
00:08:36.227 --> 00:08:37.241
if you will.

175
00:08:37.241 --> 00:08:40.227
There are other people who have done

176
00:08:40.227 --> 00:08:41.243
similar kinds of things,

177
00:08:41.243 --> 00:08:44.124
but Reich was one of the first, if not the first

