situation of dysfunctional cultures,

518
00:24:55.282 --> 00:24:57.394
and this is, of course, a terrible taboo,

519
00:24:57.394 --> 00:24:59.655
you're not supposed to talk about other cultures like this,

520
00:24:59.655 --> 00:25:01.767
because we begin to have,

521
00:25:01.767 --> 00:25:04.242
if you begin to make so-called value judgments.

522
00:25:04.242 --> 00:25:06.214
Well, I think it is important

523
00:25:06.214 --> 00:25:08.039
that you make these kind of value judgments.

524
00:25:08.039 --> 00:25:12.455
If you remember, well, none of us were alive at this time,

525
00:25:12.455 --> 00:25:17.393
but during the World War II period, and immediately after,

526
00:25:17.393 --> 00:25:20.241
the scholars of the day tried to understand

527
00:25:20.241 --> 00:25:21.926
what the hell went on with Germany,

528
00:25:21.926 --> 00:25:24.240
where this high-technology culture

529
00:25:24.240 --> 00:25:26.758
of great intellectual sophistication,

530
00:25:26.758 --> 00:25:27.856
<v Regina>And artistic.</v>

531
00:25:27.856 --> 00:25:31.397
<v James>A great culture of art and science,</v>

532
00:25:31.397 --> 00:25:33.509
collapsed into this fascism, what went on?

533
00:25:33.509 --> 00:25:37.029
So you had what they called "national character studies."

534
00:25:37.029 --> 00:25:40.175
Today that is taboo.

535
00:25:40.175 --> 00:25:42.106
Nobody studies national character anymore,

536
00:25:42.106 --> 00:25:45.135
because everything has to be equalized.

537
00:25:45.135 --> 00:25:48.078
And I ran into this in the universities,

538
00:25:48.078 --> 00:25:50.799
because my Saharasia work was the antithesis of that,

539
00:25:50.799 --> 00:25:52.505
It brought back this whole issue of

540
00:25:52.505 --> 00:25:56.425
making careful judgments about

541
00:25:56.425 --> 00:25:58.174
how people raise their kids

542
00:25:58.174 --> 00:26:01.607
and what influenced the larger society in terms of

543
00:26:01.607 --> 00:26:03.742
the potentials for violence.

544
00:26:03.742 --> 00:26:07.424
So this kind of work is talked about more outside

545
00:26:07.424 --> 00:26:09.970
of the universities than within them, unfortunately.

546
00:26:09.970 --> 00:26:14.418
because the universities... they're not very tolerant

547
00:26:14.418 --> 00:26:16.860
towards this kind of discussion,

548
00:26:16.860 --> 00:26:17.831
anymore than they are...

549
00:26:17.831 --> 00:26:19.281
<v Regina>Because it's not politically, P.C.</v>

550
00:26:19.281 --> 00:26:21.351
<v James>It's very un-P.C., isn't it?</v>

551
00:26:21.351 --> 00:26:23.377
<v Regina>So, why did you go for it?</v>

552
00:26:23.377 --> 00:26:25.905
I want to know what you know.

553
00:26:25.905 --> 00:26:29.595
<v James>Okay, well, I did that work,</v>

554
00:26:29.595 --> 00:26:32.912
but I also did another bit of heretical work,

555
00:26:32.912 --> 00:26:36.368
while I was still in the universities, and that is...

556
00:26:36.368 --> 00:26:39.899
It comes out of my interest in deserts, and desertification,

557
00:26:39.899 --> 00:26:41.733
the whole issue of spreading deserts, because,

558
00:26:41.733 --> 00:26:44.186
<v Regina>We're in that era now.</v>

559
00:26:44.186 --> 00:26:46.928
<v James>This was my classical research work, was deserts,</v>

560
00:26:46.928 --> 00:26:49.957
and what could you do to green deserts?

561
00:26:49.957 --> 00:26:52.005
And there's this guy, Wilhelm Reich,

562
00:26:52.005 --> 00:26:55.066
and he's controversial enough on Sigmund Freud

563
00:26:55.066 --> 00:26:56.975
and psychoanalysis, his sex economic work,

564
00:26:56.975 --> 00:26:58.234
if he had just stopped there,

565
00:26:58.234 --> 00:27:00.143
his name would be written into history

566
00:27:00.143 --> 00:27:01.327
in a very positive way,

567
00:27:01.327 --> 00:27:04.761
but late in his life, he's doing all this work on bioenergy,

568
00:27:04.761 --> 00:27:07.321
and orgone energy, and the accumulator,

569
00:27:07.321 --> 00:27:10.158
orgone accumulator, and he gets into trouble

570
00:27:10.158 --> 00:27:11.481
with the Food and Drug administration,

571
00:27:11.481 --> 00:27:13.550
and they burn his books and throw him in jail.

572
00:27:13.550 --> 00:27:14.915
Hey, I'm curious!

573
00:27:14.915 --> 00:27:17.560
I'm the kind of guy if I hear it's been banned in Boston,

574
00:27:17.560 --> 00:27:20.706
I wanna know why is it banned in Boston?

575
00:27:20.706 --> 00:27:24.461
So then the most outrageous thing,

576
00:27:24.461 --> 00:27:27.832
outrageous in a good way, I would say,

577
00:27:27.832 --> 00:27:29.805
that Reich was claiming was that

578
00:27:29.805 --> 00:27:33.463
this energy that's in out bodies extends out

579
00:27:33.463 --> 00:27:35.331
into the atmosphere.

580
00:27:35.331 --> 00:27:38.540
There's a field of this energy surrounding the Earth,

581
00:27:38.540 --> 00:27:42.721
and it has variations in it,

582
00:27:42.721 --> 00:27:45.346
in the way that it moves,

583
00:27:45.346 --> 00:27:48.843
it's a pulsatory energy continuum.

584
00:27:48.843 --> 00:27:50.850
He says it goes out into space,

585
00:27:50.850 --> 00:27:53.633
like the old ether theories of 19th century physics,

586
00:27:53.633 --> 00:27:56.887
And one of the devices that he developed

587
00:27:56.887 --> 00:27:59.083
which led him to this conclusion,

588
00:27:59.083 --> 00:28:01.537
is called the cloud buster.

589
00:28:01.537 --> 00:28:03.445
So I'm looking at this and saying, cloud buster,

590
00:28:03.445 --> 00:28:05.280
wow, that's fascinating,

591
00:28:05.280 --> 00:28:09.013
here I know some of Reich's other work is true,

592
00:28:09.013 --> 00:28:10.678
because I've tested it out myself,

593
00:28:10.678 --> 00:28:12.756
I also tested the orgone energy accumulator,

594
00:28:12.756 --> 00:28:14.293
which we can talk about,

595
00:28:14.293 --> 00:28:16.373
but I tested out cloud busters, as well,

596
00:28:16.373 --> 00:28:18.442
as part of my university research,

597
00:28:18.442 --> 00:28:20.009
I built one of these devices,

598
00:28:20.009 --> 00:28:22.996
I went to some of the scholars in the United States

599
00:28:22.996 --> 00:28:27.495
that had studied with Reich, and I studied with them,

600
00:28:27.495 --> 00:28:29.584
so I would get it right,

601
00:28:29.584 --> 00:28:32.624
and I built one of these devices

602
00:28:32.624 --> 00:28:33.830
and we tested it out

603
00:28:33.830 --> 00:28:36.869
and used the database of a weather

604
00:28:36.869 --> 00:28:39.515
precipitation and cloud-cover data

605
00:28:39.515 --> 00:28:40.933
from the state of Kansas,

606
00:28:40.933 --> 00:28:43.824
and proved that this device actually could influence

607
00:28:43.824 --> 00:28:48.005
the weather over a large, statewide region.

608
00:28:48.505 --> 00:28:52.204
And this was a mind-blower, because this was

609
00:28:52.204 --> 00:28:55.244
as big a controversy for physics and meteorology

610
00:28:55.244 --> 00:28:59.329
as the other stuff was for sociology and psychology.

611
00:29:02.939 --> 00:29:05.867
So that work I continued with privately,

612
00:29:05.867 --> 00:29:09.108
because I tried to get funding and so forth,

613
00:29:09.108 --> 00:29:12.383
and it was difficult.

614
00:29:12.383 --> 00:29:15.395
It's hard to say what led

615
00:29:15.395 --> 00:29:17.555
to my basic excommunication

616
00:29:17.555 --> 00:29:19.088
from the academic world.

617
00:29:19.088 --> 00:29:21.645
<v Regina>Sounds like a bit of everything.</v>

618
00:29:21.645 --> 00:29:24.994
<v James>Combined with verifying Reich's sex-economic work,</v>

619
00:29:24.994 --> 00:29:28.247
with Saharasia, and then getting positive results

620
00:29:28.247 --> 00:29:29.260
on the cloud buster,

621
00:29:29.260 --> 00:29:32.065
see, a lot of my colleges thought, well, Demeo,

622
00:29:32.065 --> 00:29:34.519
he's just doing another one of his crazy things,

623
00:29:34.519 --> 00:29:36.383
he'll test the cloud buster and he'll show

624
00:29:36.383 --> 00:29:38.600
that it doesn't work.

625
00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:40.382
I mean, I've always been an honest academic,

626
00:29:40.382 --> 00:29:42.921
I'm gonna go with what the data says,

627
00:29:42.921 --> 00:29:45.054
and I got positive results,

628
00:29:45.054 --> 00:29:47.049
so this stunned a lot of people.

629
00:29:47.049 --> 00:29:50.174
I had supporters, I had detractors,

630
00:29:50.174 --> 00:29:52.679
and for about 10 years, I continued

631
00:29:52.679 --> 00:29:55.048
teaching in different universities.

632
00:29:55.048 --> 00:29:59.090
After I left University of Kansas, I was teaching

633
00:29:59.090 --> 00:30:02.716
at Illinois State University, and a few years later

634
00:30:02.716 --> 00:30:05.575
at the University of Miami in South Florida,

635
00:30:05.575 --> 00:30:08.988
then at the University of Northern Iowa,

636
00:30:08.988 --> 00:30:11.122
and at that point it was clear,

637
00:30:11.122 --> 00:30:12.508
I was one of these guys that,

638
00:30:12.508 --> 00:30:14.151
thank you for your service,

639
00:30:14.151 --> 00:30:16.828
you've taught here for three years, adios,

640
00:30:16.828 --> 00:30:18.641
and then go to the next place,

641
00:30:18.641 --> 00:30:19.996
and you work there for another three years,

642
00:30:19.996 --> 00:30:22.844
and you don't get the tenure-track positions

643
00:30:22.844 --> 00:30:24.731
if you're doing controversial work,

644
00:30:24.731 --> 00:30:26.929
so I decided at some point I should

645
00:30:26.929 --> 00:30:30.832
devote myself through my own institute,

646
00:30:30.832 --> 00:30:32.635
which is what I did in 1988,

647
00:30:32.635 --> 00:30:34.523
I stepped out of the university system

648
00:30:34.523 --> 00:30:37.211
and just began going for my own institute.

649
00:30:37.211 --> 00:30:41.136
Now, it's interesting, right at that time,

650
00:30:41.136 --> 00:30:44.848
some of my work began to be published,

651
00:30:44.848 --> 00:30:48.058
and got to be known,

652
00:30:48.058 --> 00:30:52.655
I was presenting my work to some of the scholarly societies,

653
00:30:52.655 --> 00:30:55.866
like the Association of Arid Lands Studies,

654
00:30:55.866 --> 00:30:57.775
and the American Association of Geographers,

655
00:30:57.775 --> 00:31:01.615
and through this network of different people,

656
00:31:01.615 --> 00:31:03.790
and working outside the universities,

657
00:31:03.790 --> 00:31:06.379
I was asked

658
00:31:06.379 --> 00:31:10.768
to undertake some research projects,

659
00:31:10.768 --> 00:31:13.173
some application projects for drought abatement

660
00:31:13.173 --> 00:31:15.365
in different parts of the world.

661
00:31:15.365 --> 00:31:19.745
I had done a study in Arizona

662
00:31:19.745 --> 00:31:22.145
applying Reich's cloud buster

663
00:31:22.145 --> 00:31:23.781
in 1989, for example,

664
00:31:23.781 --> 00:31:26.991
and it was on five pre-announced dates,

665
00:31:26.991 --> 00:31:29.497
went into Arizona, used this cloud busting device

666
00:31:29.497 --> 00:31:31.098
for a couple of days, then went home,

667
00:31:31.098 --> 00:31:33.434
and after a whole summer of doing this,

668
00:31:33.434 --> 00:31:35.951
we took the data, aggregated it for something like

669
00:31:35.951 --> 00:31:38.894
4 or 500 rain stations in the region,

670
00:31:38.894 --> 00:31:41.498
and it was able to show

671
00:31:41.498 --> 00:31:44.514
that the rainfall

672
00:31:44.514 --> 00:31:47.364
is going along like so and we do our cloud busting work,

673
00:31:47.364 --> 00:31:49.742
and there's a leap upwards, a doubling

674
00:31:49.742 --> 00:31:52.014
of the amount of rain for about a week

675
00:31:52.014 --> 00:31:54.052
after each one of these tests.

676
00:31:54.052 --> 00:31:56.932
So we got a rainfall doubling effect over immense areas.

677
00:31:56.932 --> 00:31:58.767
<v Regina>And the rainfall is monsoon season in Arizona,</v>

678
00:31:58.767 --> 00:32:00.408
so this is when you'd be doing that,

679
00:32:00.408 --> 00:32:01.838
that's why the summer there, right?

680
00:32:01.838 --> 00:32:03.929
That's when there's a natural accumulation?

681
00:32:03.929 --> 00:32:06.340
<v James>Starting from May through...</v>

682
00:32:06.340 --> 00:32:08.579
May, June, July, August,

683
00:32:08.579 --> 00:32:09.753
about through September.

684
00:32:09.753 --> 00:32:11.608
<v Regina>Which, that's the perfect time to do it.</v>

685
00:32:11.608 --> 00:32:13.145
So you could really see the steps.

686
00:32:13.145 --> 00:32:15.095
<v James>So you could see the effects,</v>

687
00:32:15.095 --> 00:32:17.560
it wasn't really trying to break a drought,

688
00:32:17.560 --> 00:32:21.443
just so much as to see if the rainfall statistics there

689
00:32:21.443 --> 00:32:23.896
would match what we got in Kansas,

690
00:32:23.896 --> 00:32:25.741
working in a desert region

691
00:32:25.741 --> 00:32:29.623
in the desert Southwest, and it did.

692
00:32:29.623 --> 00:32:32.087
So this was a breakthrough because it showed

693
00:32:32.087 --> 00:32:34.722
the same technology that would work

694
00:32:34.722 --> 00:32:37.024
in relatively wet conditions of Kansas

695
00:32:37.024 --> 00:32:39.894
would also work in dry lands like Arizona.

696
00:32:39.894 --> 00:32:43.616
And nobody has, cloud seeding generally won't work

697
00:32:43.616 --> 00:32:46.133
in a dry land area if you don't have

698
00:32:46.133 --> 00:32:47.637
pre-existing cloud cover.

699
00:32:47.637 --> 00:32:51.233
So then I got an invitation from

700
00:32:51.233 --> 00:32:55.168
the government of Israel,

701
00:32:55.168 --> 00:32:58.015
so I was asked by the Israeli government

702
00:32:58.015 --> 00:33:00.330
during a period of drought,

703
00:33:00.330 --> 00:33:02.143
they had about three years of drought,

704
00:33:02.143 --> 00:33:06.367
with the lowest level of their main reservoir,

705
00:33:06.367 --> 00:33:09.289
Lake Kinneret, which we call the Sea of Galilee,

706
00:33:09.289 --> 00:33:12.585
was down to about one centimeter above the red line,

707
00:33:12.585 --> 00:33:15.753
which means they only have that much water left

708
00:33:15.753 --> 00:33:18.355
before they were no longer allowed to take water out

709
00:33:18.355 --> 00:33:20.137
so it would have been a catastrophe

710
00:33:20.137 --> 00:33:21.395
for their agriculture,

711
00:33:21.395 --> 00:33:25.384
so they asked me to come there and try this device out,

712
00:33:25.384 --> 00:33:29.626
which I did, and we worked it for about,

713
00:33:29.626 --> 00:33:33.970
about ten days on and off at different stations in Israel,

714
00:33:33.970 --> 00:33:37.235
and then with a final operation that was

715
00:33:37.235 --> 00:33:39.390
designed to bring in the jet stream

716
00:33:39.390 --> 00:33:41.971
and big pulses of moisture,

717
00:33:41.971 --> 00:33:44.735
and within a couple of days,

718
00:33:44.735 --> 00:33:47.166
they had the biggest rainstorm they'd had

719
00:33:47.166 --> 00:33:50.218
in those three-year periods,

720
00:33:50.218 --> 00:33:52.828
and one of the things

721
00:33:52.828 --> 00:33:54.314
that this cloud busting device does is,

722
00:33:54.314 --> 00:33:58.421
restores what Reich called "atmospheric pulsation"

723
00:33:58.421 --> 00:34:02.911
so you use it and then it's like acupuncture,

724
00:34:02.911 --> 00:34:06.142
you get the energy flow restored,

725
00:34:06.142 --> 00:34:08.947
and there's a natural pulsation that gets set up,

726
00:34:08.947 --> 00:34:13.640
of rain, dry, rain, dry, like in nature,

727
00:34:13.640 --> 00:34:18.003
it restores the natural energetic pulsation,

728
00:34:18.003 --> 00:34:20.381
and the rains come afterwards.

729
00:34:20.381 --> 00:34:23.229
And that's what happened, throughout the whole rainy season

730
00:34:23.229 --> 00:34:27.634
of that year, '91, which was their wintertime period

731
00:34:27.634 --> 00:34:29.607
when the get all their rains,

732
00:34:29.607 --> 00:34:31.741
they had these immense pulses of rain fall

733
00:34:31.741 --> 00:34:35.303
and it broke all their records going back 100 years.

734
00:34:35.303 --> 00:34:38.087
They had more rain during that one wintertime period

735
00:34:38.087 --> 00:34:42.332
than they had previously in 100 years of record keeping.

736
00:34:42.332 --> 00:34:45.788
Lake Kinneret filled to overflowing,

737
00:34:45.788 --> 00:34:49.180
they had to open the dam that allowed the sweetwater

738
00:34:49.180 --> 00:34:52.635
to go into the Dead Sea, which, in Israel, is unheard of

739
00:34:52.635 --> 00:34:54.907
because that is a so-called waste of water,

740
00:34:54.907 --> 00:34:57.413
but they had to because otherwise, it would have flooded

741
00:34:57.413 --> 00:34:59.974
the coastal cities of Tiberius and other villages

742
00:34:59.974 --> 00:35:01.595
around the lake, so they opened the dam

743
00:35:01.595 --> 00:35:04.240
and let the water go as it did by nature

744
00:35:04.240 --> 00:35:07.365
years before irrigation agriculture got started.

745
00:35:07.365 --> 00:35:09.136
And it was an immense breakthrough,

746
00:35:09.136 --> 00:35:12.037
I thought, now we're gonna get some support,

747
00:35:12.037 --> 00:35:14.682
some serious openness, we can start applying this,

748
00:35:14.682 --> 00:35:16.571
we'll green the Negev.

749
00:35:16.571 --> 00:35:17.444
<v Regina>Yeah.</v>

750
00:35:17.444 --> 00:35:19.460
<v James>It didn't happen,</v>

751
00:35:19.460 --> 00:35:21.999
because the meteorologists were against it.

752
00:35:21.999 --> 00:35:25.391
They claim, they're like classical medical doctors are

753
00:35:25.391 --> 00:35:27.460
to alternative medical treatments, you know?

754
00:35:27.460 --> 00:35:30.126
The meteorologists, they said, well,

755
00:35:30.126 --> 00:35:32.280
This, your cloud busting had nothing to do with it,

756
00:35:32.280 --> 00:35:35.342
it had to do with Mount Pinatubo

757
00:35:35.342 --> 00:35:38.083
erupting on the other side of the Earth six months earlier.

758
00:35:38.083 --> 00:35:39.854
<v Regina>Oh, well.</v>

759
00:35:39.854 --> 00:35:42.616
<v James>Oh well, okay, so I got another good data set</v>

760
00:35:42.616 --> 00:35:44.611
and we showed the results,

761
00:35:44.611 --> 00:35:46.371
I published a good paper about it,

762
00:35:46.371 --> 00:35:50.274
and I had two other major projects

763
00:35:50.274 --> 00:35:54.071
that came in the '90's, one was in Namibia,

764
00:35:54.071 --> 00:35:57.570
where another three or four year drought ongoing,

765
00:35:57.570 --> 00:36:00.438
the whole Southern part of Africa affected,

766
00:36:00.438 --> 00:36:02.914
there, they were looking at starvation.

767
00:36:02.914 --> 00:36:04.278
<v Regina>Same results?</v>

768
00:36:04.278 --> 00:36:06.241
<v James>Same kind of results, very positive,</v>

769
00:36:06.241 --> 00:36:08.129
breakthrough in rains,

770
00:36:11.539 --> 00:36:16.362
and the guy who ran their meteorology department was a...

771
00:36:16.372 --> 00:36:20.742
Afrikaaner, Christian guy,

772
00:36:20.742 --> 00:36:23.294
a boor type,

773
00:36:23.294 --> 00:36:27.177
very fundamentalistic fellow,

774
00:36:27.177 --> 00:36:29.491
and when I went into the office to meet him,

